@Jon Onstot 

I, at some point, got it confused with "parge," which is the use of mortar or cement on the outer surfaces of blocks, bricks, etc. in order to give a wall a smooth surface and to seal it. Mostly I know about it from repairing damage to my house done by the previous owner's misuse of the technique by using it on weight-bearing horizontal surfaces.

I actually used to brew beer, and have "sparged" grain in the process of making wort, but years of demolishing  parged-over broken cinder block stairs  and threshholds with the thin cracked layer of mortar falling away from broken blocks made "parge" eclipse "sparge" in my mind.

