@Peter C.
As a (former) home-brewer, it took me an extra beat to come up with SPARGE but it is indeed a term for the hot water sprinkled over “MASHed” grains (mainly barley), to extract additional “WORT”.  The mashed grains are held in the “LAUTER TUN” prior to SPARGing, and that vessel has a false bottom that allows the wort to pass through, while filtering out the spent grains.  (And at this point we haven’t even added hops - much less the yeast required to convert the MALTOSE to alcohol)

Ah yes, brewing and it’s resplendent jargon.
